Class Suit

  • java.lang.Object
    • bramspr.Suit

  • public class Suit
extends java.lang.Object
    Instances of this class indicate the suit for entities in a Bramspr-program, such as variables, function return values, expressions, type-denoters, et cetera. Suits are a concept like types: they are a property of an entity in a program. They can be returned, denoted and compared. Practically, they bundle a type and a constancy. BramsprChecker makes extensive use of this class, using it as the return type for its visit-methods.
